HEADWORD: Underfringe
<hw>Un"der*fringe`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lower fringe;
a fringe underneath something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Broad-faced, with <qex>underfringe</qex> of russet beard.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

